title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta 96F Brigadier Boarder Marshal Special NEW IN BOX.
postcontent:
The Beretta 96F Brigadier Boarder Marshal Special .40s&w was originally specifically made for the US Boarder Patrol in 2000, then the Boarder Patrol backed out. Only 2000 of this model were ever made. It has a the heavy slide, shorter 4.7 barrel, government hammer, and all metal parts.

This pistol is not like new in box is NEW IN BOX. It has never been fired or even loaded. It comes with two 10 round mags. Two sets of grips came with the pistol, the hard plastic and the wide Brigadier rubber grips. It is fitted with the original Trilux night sight which are much like the Trijicon and are starting to fade, no worries Trijicon still makes sights for the Brigadier slide. The heavy slide is dovetailed to accept Trijicon, Meprolight, and other brand sights.

Firearm is unmodified in any way.

The Brigadier will accept modern Wilson Combat, Beretta, Bar Sto, and KKM parts. Can accept 4.9 barrels, and higher capacity magazines. And can be used with 9mm by changing barrel, recoil spring, and extractor as with most .40 caliber pistols. 

While I have not fired this particular 96f Brigadier. The Brigadier is the best firing 40s&w handgun IMO.

MAKE OPENING OFFER. Price is negotiable. Local exchanges only, no FFL transfers, no low ball offers.

title: For Sale:  BRAND NEW PEPPER SPRAY KEYCHAIN, HARD CASE, BLACK IN COLOR...**FREE REFILLS FOR LIFE
postcontent: Pepper Spray Keychain, hard case, black in color If you ever use your "pepper spray" in self-defense, send me a copy of the police report and you'll get free refills. ================= About Pepper Spray: This spray has an Ultra-Violet Light Identifying Dye (which helps to ID these Ass-holes) includes both a clip (to easily attach it to your clothes while walking) and a key ring. PEPPER SPRAY FACTS: Pepper spray enables you to defend yourself while keeping a safe distance from an attacker. Pepper sprays induce an almost immediate burning sensation of the skin and a burning, tearing, and swelling of the eyes. If spray is inhaled, the respiratory tract becomes inflamed resulting in a swelling of the mucous membranes lining the breathing passages and temporarily restricting breathing to short, shallow breaths. A one second burst to the face will cause temporary blindness, choking, coughing, and nausea-disabling your attacker giving you time to escape. The active ingredient in this spray is Oleoresin Capsicum (O.C.), commonly referred to as red pepper. It is a natural, oily, resin-like substance derived from hot peppers, the same peppers used to make spicy foods hot. When considering which pepper spray is most effective, one must consider the percentage of pepper being used and the heat rating of that pepper (measured in Scoville Heat Units or S.H.U.). A good pepper sprays has a rating of 2 million S.H.U. or higher... **Don't be fooled by the claims "Hottest allowed by law" and "Hottest in the industry" that are made by some on the web. This gives people a false sense of security.** FYI...Capsaicinoid Concentration is the determination of active components in Oleoresin Capsicum. Capsaicinoids are the group of compounds that cause the burning sensation. There are the three main compounds that make up about 95% of the Capsaicinoids: Capsaicin, Dihydrocapsaicin, and Nordihydrocapsaicin. The Capsaicinoid Concentration is the amount of these compounds in a certain solution. Therefore, by measuring the amount of capsaicinoids, an accurate level of pungency can be determined for the solution. This is the unit of measurement that is the most consistent and best representation throughout all grades of Oleoresin Capsicum. In essence, it is the equaling factor between SHU’s and % OC. While the strength of the selected peppers may vary from year to year or between seasons, the measurement of capsaicinoids is consistent in determining that hotness. A 0.2% Capsaicinoid Concentration will yield the same amount of hotness, regardless of the batch of peppers or their location of cultivation. For this reason, it is the only accurate method of determining the pungency of peppers. The current detection method for this analysis is by High-Performance Liquid Chromatography, HPLC.4 Therefore, by establishing quality control monitoring the capsaicinoid concentration, a consistent strength or pungency can be easily obtained and verified by this analysis. **Federal law does not allow carrying any type of pepper spray on airplanes or in the security areas of an airport. They are also prohibited on aircraft because the drop in air pressure can cause the pepper spray canisters to explode. For the same reason, pepper spray cannot be shipped by air. **If you're flying, I'll tell/show you how to make your spray "airplane safe". Just e-mail me. Always remember that you assume all risk and liability for owning and using pepper spray. Even if you use it correctly, there is no guarantee that it will always be effective at hindering an attack, and there is always the possibility that it may be used against you instead. **Consult the laws of your state and/or local agency. Understand and Obey them before owning pepper spray.** ------------------- **Revised Code of Washington 9.91.160** Personal protection spray devices. (1) It is unlawful for a person under eighteen years old, unless the person is at least fourteen years old and has the permission of a parent or guardian to do so, to purchase or possess a personal protection spray device. A violation of this subsection is a misdemeanor. (2) No town, city, county, special purpose district, quasi-municipal corporation or other unit of government may prohibit a person eighteen years old or older, or a person fourteen years old or older who has the permission of a parent or guardian to do so, from purchasing or possessing a personal protection spray device or from using such a device in a manner consistent with the authorized use of force under RCW 9A.16.020. No town, city, county, special purpose district, quasi-municipal corporation, or other unit of government may prohibit a person eighteen years old or older from delivering a personal protection spray device to a person authorized to possess such a device. (3) For purposes of this section: (a) "Personal protection spray device" means a commercially available dispensing device designed and intended for use in self-defense and containing a non-lethal sternutator or lacrimator agent, including but not limited to: (i) Tear gas, the active ingredient of which is either chloracetophenone (CN) or O-chlorobenzylidene malonotrile (CS); or (ii) Other agent commonly known as mace, pepper mace, or pepper gas. (b) "Delivering" means actual, constructive, or attempted transferring from one person to another. (4) Nothing in this section authorizes the delivery, purchase, possession, or use of any device or chemical agent that is otherwise prohibited by state law. =========================== Here are 2 (two) “Pepper Spray” Videos... http://www.ebaumsworld.com/video/watch/959530/ http://www.snotr.com/video/1533 (a little clip from "The Office" on pepper spray)I can meet you in Redmond, Seattle, Woodinville, Lake Forest Park, Kenmore, Duvall and North Bend.

title: For Sale:  RARE WWII Victory Model .38 Smith & Wesson Aussie
postcontent:
Rare WWII Victory Model .38 Smith & Wesson 5" barrel. Rare due to the letters FTR engraved on the right side near S&W crest. The Smith and Wesson forum explains it as follows:

This revolver was likely shipped from the S&W factory in the 1943-1944 time frame. From the markings you provided it is evident that your Victory served with the Australian military, as it bears the FTR rebuild markings that are so often seen on the Aussie guns. Most of the Aussie guns seen here today underwent a rebuild process in the 1950s.The gun has been FTR (factory thorough rebuild) probably at Lithgow, but that is where the original grips probably got parted from the gun.

This gun has S&W diamond walnut grips, if you remove them you can see much deeper bluing. The Victory model used a smooth walnut grip still available on Ebay for $12-20.
Also missing is the lanyard loop available for $20-30 on various websites. The barrel, frame and cylinder numbers match. This gun was blued rather than the standard "Magic Black" sand blasted or Parkerized finish. The finish is worn to a nice patina, overall it is in great shape for a gun 70+ years old. I tried to show the mirror bright quality of the bore. There are no other military markings on this gun. I cannot guarantee the information from the S&W forum is 100% accurate but it does have some of the most knowledgeable experts on this model. 

FTF sale preferred, must have valid Wisconsin ID or will ship to FFL holder. Items are sold as is, no warranty. No scammers or low ballers please. 
Owner may be interested in trading for S&W M&P Shield or left handed .22s.

title: For Sale/Trade:  17 HMR Marlin 100% tuned and upgraded (Competition &  Zombie ready)
postcontent:
I'm moving to an area that doesn't have rimfire class match clubs, so rather than have a "safe queen" here is my uber-tuned sub, sub, sub MOA accurate rimfire competition rifle, trigger, scope, stock... Everything but a silencer, ****plus several hundred rounds of ammo**** all from the same lot except one box I use for PD's.

The photo below was shot off the bipod, 100yds, 7 to 11mph wind, 10 shots. The group would be half that size without the blustery wind, without a doubt. 

3 magazines: two 10 round and one 5 round.

This is my "go-to" rifle for any rimfire competition. It never let me down and the rounds scream so fast, they are almost laser-accurate. It's almost an unfair advantage, going up against .22LR with this.

This rifle is Zombie, Germ Outbreak and Prairie Dog removal ready. The power and explosive nature of the ammunition makes an unparalleled paper puncher, varminter or just plain fun 300 yard plinker. YES, I said out to 300 yards, with a .17! It's that good of a round.

If you use the software app "STRELOK", plug in your ballistic data, it will give you instant firing solutions for every distance, including atmospheric inputs. Simply hold-over or dial in your windage and elevation and you're ALWAYS on, as long as you do your part too!

From 30 yds to 150 yds, prairie dogs nearly explode, at 200, it is still a little messy-goopy shot and (of course) they are DRT, however, I've pushed it to 315 and dropped them with one clean hit. I have no doubt you could go further if you were using paper targets.

The stock and finish is in immaculate shape. This is NOT an off-the-shelf Marlin, the wood is shiny as glass, there is laser stippling on the forend and grip and the optics are very nice.

You'd be hard pressed to find fault in this weapon. It operates perfectly, I don't believe it has any "felt recoil" with the heavy barrel, as you can see the bullet impact even with the scope on high power, and it flat-out looks cool.

The trigger is wonderful and responsive. It doesn't have any grit or an inappropriately heavy pull. I've had people tell me it feels like a rack and pinion steering race car wheel on ball bearings - they can feel the entire draw and feedback, smooth and accurate.

Please email me through here or text 4O99398903. I'm Robert. Let me know if you need different photos or anything else. I'm at your disposal. 

Wyoming FTF rules apply as always.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Mosin 1891 7.62x54R Shoots 1.2 MOA
postcontent:
Price includes a CRATE of ammo!

Totally Armory fresh, but with 13 hashes in the side of the stock. Serial number, a trace and homework on the armory stamps show it likely saw the end of WWII then guard duty before being crated and stored. I purchased crates of these, TT's, Tokarovs, SKS's and a few AK74's directly from the Red's armories while on deployment to East Europe with the USMC and imported via my best friend's company. 

Comes with a CRATE of ammo. See pics. 

Bayonet included... Probably 2 feet long. Also has a small service and cleaning kit. 

Upgraded rear leaf sight to diopter style and this WILL shoot within about 1.2 MOA out to 900yds without even a second thought. If you don't like the rear sight, I kept the Russian leaf. A simple pin and spring will swap them.

This is one BAMF rifle. Harvested a share of Caribou and a Moose while on hunts in Alaska, using Russian ammo. Bears = DRT.

Comes with that giant case of ammo PLUS RCBS reloading dies and 20 S&B loaded brass bullets if you want to reload right away or simply not shoot USSR ammo. 

When this was unpacked, it had a habit of sending fliers up and to the left. The barrel was recrowned ever so slightly which corrected the gasses not exiting equally from the crown... and the barrel is in a slightly better condition than most others that are out there.

 Again, it will shoot just over 1MOA using milsurp ammo. I don't doubt you could do a minute or less on handloaded brass.

As soon as this was uncrated at my friend's business, I hand picked this one and gave it the royal treatment. The barrel was corked, all parts degreased, treated, and repolished, which took about a week. 

I do not have any details about the "13" engraved in the stock. We suspect it was either combat kills or months in service.

Headstamp is 1943, Tula.

Text me at 4O99398903 or by sending an email through here. Privacy assured.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Spikes Zombie AR, 100% pro-built, SOCOM Blue Cerakote; One of a kind!
postcontent:
JUST IN TIME FOR CHRISTMAS, a one-of-a-kind pro built AR. 

The upload limits here don't let me have a clear shot so I apologize that you can't really see the color.  "SOCOM Blue" is darker than Navy Blue, it is very, very dark and subtle, but just beautiful in the sun. The pics just can't do it justice, sorry. I've been trying to get good ones and it isn't working out.

I need to thin out the extras in my AR safe, getting ready to build some new ones, I wish I had time to shoot this one, because it is one of my favorites besides the SIG x1 carbon.

Let's get down to brass tacks... It's 100% pro built with ALL premium components. ONLY TEST FIRED, operates flawlessly. 6 shots to zero optic and iron sights, 14 shots to check BDC ranges in optic. (20 total) Cleaned, put away. Barrel is considered "properly broken in" by popular method.

Build data:

Lower:

-Spikes Tactical 7075 Lower with "Live, Dead, Undead" switch settings (see pic)

-Palmetto premium M4 stock, Buffer Spring and buffer

-Preeeeeeeemium tuned trigger, polished everything, ceramic-embedded lube surfaces. (Best AR trigger I've owned or shot)

-Ceramic surface coats on sear/disconnect/hammer/friction surfaces and Teflon lube at lugs, doesn't feel gritty, won't walk out pins or leak shit everywhere, (because that collects dust and we don't like that).

-Ambidextrous single point sling mount for right handed shooters and southpaws too!

-Ambi safety selectors

-Hogue grip

-Enhanced Trigger Guard

Upper:

-Nearly everything on the upper is Cerakote SOCOM Blue (pics are hard to see but it's sexy) Barrel, receiver rear cap, castle nut, D-ring, handguards, Flash suppressor, almost everything we could possibly do. 

-Internals are Black Phosphate with chrome contact surfaces and stainless rings. (Military testing showed that using other coatings or chrome besides the phosphate only extends the anti-foul by 100 rounds. AR/M4 always foul, nearly scientifically at 2,450 rds if you don't clean it)

-Barrel is a new SIG Tactical Designated Marksman 1:7 twist, will stabilize up to 90gr subsonics and will drive tacks with 75 and 77 grain 5.56 NATO loads (barrel is SOCOM Blue)

-Carbine length gas system, flat top front rail with 45 degree back up iron sight
Spikes upper (SOCOM Blue)

-Standard charging handle, as a Marine, I just don't feel that is a useful upgrade, but if you want it, I'll put on the BCM gunfighter Ambi.

-Wylde chamber (shoots .223 and 5.56 NATO without having extraction issues. It's just better. Go Wylde.)

-SIG ARMS bolt, carrier group and cam with all premium polish and lube on appropriate areas only, not drowned in CLP!

-Dampened extractor (brass doesn't fly 40 feet away, it is tamed down to about 12 feet) if you want brass to fly far again, simply remove the extractor spring donut.

-PROFESSIONALLY HEADSPACED, torque checked and timed by SIG armorer, re-checked by my armorer, no messing around there. Safety is king.

-Titanium firing pin to reduce severity of light primer strikes when rounds chamber. (I have never seen an AD from a firing pin, but I wanted to build this right.

-Flat top receiver

-Plain Ejection Port Cover, ready for your customizing or for a Strike Industries door clip

-45 degree back up iron sights (BZO is dead on)

Option: Prismatic 3x SIG TAC scope with illuminated BDC reticle out to 600 yards (+$175)
Option: Magpul MOE handguards ($retail price, will install / fit for free) MOE requires a slight mod under the top grip so the front sight rail clears it. 

Everything is built to spec, torqued and indexed correctly. Match grade components on all internals and hard use items, SIG matched bolt face to chamber, 7075 aluminum in receivers (so dry firing won't bend the area in front of the hammer, which crushes 6061 aluminum receivers.)

The backup sights have mil-spec steel day/night diopters and the range roll. I tried to keep it simple and light. They hold zero and locked solid.

title: For Sale:  Original Antique Vintage German WW2 NAZI Dagger made by Robert Herder Solingen
postcontent: This German SA Dagger was originally commissioned by Hitler for members of the National Socialist German Workers Party or NSDAP (National Sozialistische Deutsche Arbeiter Partei). These daggers were designed for use as dress accessories and functioned as symbols of status and rank within the Nazi party. The design of the SA dagger, like its counterpart the SS Dagger, incorporated elements of the "Holbein" dagger which was a German hunting knife that dates back to the 16th century. One of the primary design features of the SA knife is the Nazi eagle with its wings spread wide, grasping a wreath that contains a very prominent swastika in its center. Other prominent features include the SA symbol within a circle at the top of the wooden grip, the phrase "Alles fur Deutschland" (Everything for Germany) inscribed in the center of the steel blade in Gothic script, and a distinctive curved grip fashioned from various woods including walnut, birch, and maple.  Some of the early versions of the German SA dagger exhibit some important differences compared to later knives. These include the lack of the circular SA insignia, a different phrase inscribed in the blade: Deutschland Uber Alles" (Germany Above All), and a larger nickel eagle design. However these early models of the SA dagger are extremely rare and only a small number of them are known to exist. This dagger is by maker Robert Herder, Solingen with the nice, hard to come by windmill maker mark.

title: For Sale:  1000 Round Can of 5.56mm GP21 - SS109 / M855 - 62 Grain Penetrator Ammo
postcontent:
4 unopened cans available. Firm price. Will not ship. Check out my other listings of AR-15s, optics and ammo. 

Finest quality 5.56mm ammo made in Lithuania by GGG to exceed NATO specification. This is "GP21" ball ammo which is a ss109 / M855 type load, made to stricter quality standards than NATO requires. The ammo is of course brass case, non-corrosive and reloadable boxer primer. The projectile does contain a steel penetrator and is magnetic, but it is not color coded with a green tip as is traditional with US manufactured m855. Manufactured in 2012 or 2013. Comes 50 rounds per box, 20 boxes per case. This ammo is truly some of the best real NATO mil-spec 5.56x45 ammunition ever to be offered consumer in the US market. If you are looking for top quality ammo for your AR15 or other 5.56mm caliber semi auto rifle and you will accept no substitutions then this is the ammunition to get.

Unlike most other ‘NATO’ ammunition on the market GGG GP21 is new production; not old surplus, product overrun or ‘NATO like’ imitations. GGG GP21 is 100% authentic military ammunition exceeding all STANAG and MOPI requirements. GGG manufactures and qualifies GGG GP21 ammunition to the same rigorous standards whether the end user is the US commercial market or a front line military combat unit. GGG spares no expenses in the manufacturing process using only the highest grade of brass with deep annealing that is excellent for reloading. The military grade boxer primers are non-corrosive, non-mercuric and exceed all sensitivity requirements for combat use. A high quality double base smokeless propellant is used. The full metal jackets are made from tombac. The case mouth and case primer joint have a waterproof sealing. The M2A1 cases are sealed with a full rubber gasket. There is also a wire and pressed stamp lock around the hinge which must be cut to open. As a result of both the quality manufacturing and the packaging, when stored in this fashion, GGG NATO ammunition has a minimum shelf life of no less than 20 years. GGG NATO qualified ammunition far exceeds the benchmark and typical performance of other NATO ammunition.
